# SEO Best Practices for Lilucat.com

## Meta Tags & Head Elements
- Always include proper meta title, description, and keywords in front matter
- Use descriptive, keyword-rich titles (50-60 characters max)
- Write compelling meta descriptions (150-160 characters max)
- Include Open Graph tags for social media sharing
- Add Twitter Card meta tags for better Twitter sharing
- Use canonical URLs to prevent duplicate content issues

## Image Optimization
- Always include alt text for all images (descriptive, not generic)
- Use title attributes for better accessibility and SEO
- Optimize image file sizes (use WebP format when possible)
- Include proper image dimensions (width/height attributes)
- Use descriptive filenames for images
- Implement lazy loading for images below the fold

## Link Structure
- Use descriptive, keyword-rich anchor text
- Include title attributes on all links for better UX
- Use proper rel attributes (noopener for external links)
- Implement internal linking strategy
- Ensure all links are working (no broken links)
- Use semantic HTML for better crawlability

## Content Structure
- Use proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3, etc.)
- Include one H1 per page
- Use descriptive, keyword-rich headings
- Structure content with proper HTML semantics
- Include schema markup for better search understanding
- Write content for users, optimize for search engines

## Technical SEO
- Ensure mobile-first responsive design
- Optimize page load speed
- Use clean, semantic HTML
- Implement proper URL structure
- Include sitemap.xml
- Add robots.txt file
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Implement proper redirects
- **GitHub Pages specific**: Use meta tags for security headers (no _headers file support)
- **GitHub Pages specific**: Optimize for bandwidth limitations and CDN

## Local SEO (if applicable)
- Include business information consistently
- Use local keywords in content
- Implement local schema markup
- Ensure NAP (Name, Address, Phone) consistency

## Performance
- Minimize CSS and JavaScript
- Optimize images and use appropriate formats
- Use CDN for static assets
- Implement caching strategies
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

## Accessibility
- Include alt text for all images
- Use proper ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure proper color contrast
- Make sure keyboard navigation works
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Content Guidelines
- Write unique, valuable content
- Use natural language and avoid keyword stuffing
- Include relevant keywords naturally in content
- Update content regularly
- Use internal linking to related content
- Include calls-to-action where appropriate

## Social Media
- Optimize Open Graph images (1200x630px recommended)
- Include social media meta tags
- Use engaging social media descriptions
- Implement social sharing buttons

## Analytics & Tracking
- Implement Google Analytics properly
- Set up Google Search Console
- Track user behavior and engagement
- Monitor search performance
- Use proper event tracking

## Code Quality
- Write clean, semantic HTML
- Use proper indentation and formatting
- Comment complex code sections
- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Validate HTML and CSS

## Security
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Implement proper security headers
- Keep dependencies updated
- Use secure external links (rel="noopener")
- Validate user inputs

## Mobile Optimization
- Ensure responsive design works on all devices
- Optimize touch targets (minimum 44px)
- Test on various screen sizes
- Ensure fast loading on mobile networks
- Use mobile-friendly navigation

## International SEO (if applicable)
- Use proper hreflang tags
- Implement language-specific URLs
- Translate content properly
- Consider cultural differences in content

## Monitoring & Maintenance
- Regularly check for broken links
- Monitor page load speeds
- Track search rankings
- Update content regularly
- Monitor user feedback and analytics 